The best way to get even if you don't like the product is to cancel your account and go elsewhere with your $9.95 of leisure/disposable income. You can go see one more movie a month, rent a batting cage for 30 minutes, Have a steak dinner at Denny's, A Margarita at El Torito, Take a 2 hour Drive, lots of stuff. The point here is, instead of rallying to lynch the people at Verant for introducing a new product that was not perhaps ready for release(I am glad they released it anyway), you have two choices; Play or don't.<br>
I feel your pain on the frustrations associated with this new release, but in time I think they will work it all out. Until then, I am still going to play and deal with the minor hassles and frequent patches. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umomur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Momur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/13/01 2:11:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Neverquest - a Class Action? - Discuss</span><hr size=1> The logic behind your math is F'ed. You pay per month not per hour.  It's more like $10 for the month lost + $30 for Luclin which doesn't work + $?20-40? for the other disks which are now cup coasters. ~$70 stolen.<br>
<br>
Have you ever returned a game to the store and when asked by the manager,&quot;Why are you returning it?&quot;, looked them straight in the eye and said,&quot;Because it sucks.&quot; I have. I got my money back. I'm not quite ready to do that with EQ, yet. I have faith that they'll fix it.<br>
